  • Method Details

    • add

      public void add(T object)
      ADD METHOD CHECKS IF ARRAY IS FULL. IF IT IS, GROWS IT. IF IT ISN'T, FINDS THE FIRST AVAILABLE INDEX AND STORES THE GIVEN OBJECT IN IT.
      Parameters:
      object - - THE OBJECT TO ADD

    • doubleArraySize

      private void doubleArraySize()
      CREATES A NEW, TEMPORARY ARRAY WITH DOUBLE THE SIZE. COPIES THE CONTENTS OF THE ORIGINAL ARRAY INTO THE NEW ONE. SUBSTITUTES THE OBJECT REFERENCED BY THE objects PROPERTY.

    • remove

      public void remove(int index)
      VERIFIES IF THE INDEX SPECIFIED EXISTS, AND IF IT DOES, CHECKS IF THERE'S AN ACTUAL OBJECT STORED IN IT. IF BOTH CONDITIONS ARE VERIFIED, THE OBJECT IN THE SPECIFIED POSITION WILL BE REMOVED FINALLY, IT CHECKS IF HALF THE POSITIONS OF THE ARRAY ARE EMPTY. IF THEY ARE, THE ARRAY SHRINKS IN SIZE.
      Parameters:
      index - - REPRESENTS THE INDEX WHERE THE OBJECT TO BE DELETED IS

    • moveLeft

      private void moveLeft(int index)
      MOVE ALL THE OBJECTS AFTER THE INDEX SPECIFIED TO THE LEFT.

    • shrinkArray

      private void shrinkArray()
      CREATES A NEW, TEMPORARY ARRAY, WITH HALF THE SIZE OF THE ORIGINAL ONE. COPIES THE ELEMENTS OF THE ORIGINAL ARRAY INTO THE NEW ONE. SUBSTITUTES THE OBJECT REFERENCED BY THE objects PROPERTY.
